  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Evaluation of different glycemic variations between the dialysis period and non-dialysis
      period in two groups: nondiabetic and diabetic patients undergone two different hemodialysis
      methods. Thirty-six patients, males and females, aged 50-80 years, with end stage renal
      disease (ESRD) will undergo hemodialysis and continuous glucose monitoring (CGM). The
      investigators will evaluate also inflammation markers before and after the different
      hemodialysis methods.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
